han the cash flows, someone can buy the company and take the cash flows =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0it does not put a=C2=A0ceiling=C2=A0on the price. If the stock =
has cash flows worth $10, and you want to pay $20 for it, I can=E2=80=99t s=
