n?=E2=80=9D you will fail.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t know what you should write! Th=
e textbook is not yet written. But it does seem =E2=80=94=C2=A0as an empiri=
cal matter, but also just intuitively =E2=80=94=C2=A0like a lot of people w=
ould want to buy shares of an electronic token called =E2=80=9CDJT=E2=80=9D=
 that represents their fondness for Donald Trump, that marks them out as me=
mbers of a Donald Trump-supporting club, and that actually makes Trump hims=
elf richer and supports him in his endeavors. And so they might pay money f=
or that token. And the cash flows just don=E2=80=99t enter into it at all.=
=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Again, I don=E2=80=99t think I=E2=80=99m all t=
hat serious about any of this, or at least I hope I=E2=80=99m not. But Bloo=
mberg=E2=80=99s Bailey Lipschultz <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbus=
iness.com/click/34887393.257355/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2F=
ydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDQtMDEvdHJ1bXAtbWVkaWEtbG9zdC01OC1taWxsaW9uLW9uLTQtbWlsbG=
lvbi1pbi1zYWxlcy1sYXN0LXllYXI_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDQwMTI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZ=
Gl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwNDAxJnV0bV9jYW1w=
YWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb938747b" itemprop=3D"StoryLi=
nk" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  reports t=
oday</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Trump Media &amp; Technology Group Corp.=E2=80=
=99s stock fell as much as 22% on Monday to as low as $48.03 per share, bel=
ow the $49.95 level where the blank-check vehicle it merged with was tradin=
g a week ago. The company has still delivered a meteoric gain this year to =
date, with its market value sitting at about $6.6 billion after it became a=
 meme stock and captivated retail traders.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The company generated just $4.1 million in rev=
enue for the full year, results reported in a filing Monday morning show, u=
nderscoring how richly valued Trump Media is relative to its peers. =E2=80=
=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The discrepancy between where Trump Media=E2=
=80=99s shares trade and how the underlying business performs indicates tha=
t investors use it as a way to bet on Trump=E2=80=99s push for re-election.=
 The stock, which has been trading since 2021 under the SPAC=E2=80=99s tick=
er, has tripled this year as the retail-trading crowd pumps it with posts a=
cross Stocktwits and Reddit=E2=80=99s WallStreetBets forum.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CUse it as a way to bet on Trump=E2=80=
=99s push for re-election.=E2=80=9D If he=E2=80=99s elected, will that make=
 the company=E2=80=99s business more lucrative? Oh, quite possibly; maybe h=
e=E2=80=99ll sign an executive order requiring companies to advertise on=C2=
=A0Truth Social. But I don=E2=80=99t think you have to posit a mechanism li=
ke that.=C2=A0 You can just say =E2=80=9Cpeople want to bet on Trump, so th=
ey buy Trump Media.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or Dan Primack <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bl=
oombergbusiness.com/click/34887393.257355/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYXhpb3MuY29tL25ld=
3NsZXR0ZXJzL2F4aW9zLXByby1yYXRhLTBlNjkwYjk0LThlNTktNDNhOS05NGZiLTc1NjIxNmYw=
YTU5OC5odG1s/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB014d30ec" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" item=
scope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> writes today</a> t=
hat =E2=80=9Cit=E2=80=99s not possible to even pretend that the equity valu=
e has any relation to the underlying business. At this point, owning TMTG i=
s basically an in-kind donation to Donald Trump. Both financially and reput=
ationally.=E2=80=9D Yes! A lot of people want to associate themselves with =
Donald Trump, and also for some reason want to make him richer, and Trump M=
edia=E2=80=99s stock is a quite straightforward way to do that.<a class=3D"=
footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorati=
on: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000=
; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !impo=
rtant; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a> Why does it=C2=A0<em>have=C2=A0</em>to have any relation to the underl=
ying business?=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Back when the Trump Media special purpose acqu=
isition company deal was first announced in 2021, the stock jumped, and=C2=
=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34887393.257355=
/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTAtMjEvbW=
F0dC1sZXZpbmUtcy1tb25leS1zdHVmZi1kb25hbGQtdHJ1bXAtZG9lcy1hLXNwYWM_Y21waWQ9Q=
kJEMDQwMTI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0=
ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwNDAxJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a3=
19a23cB2e903ebc" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_=
blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; =
background-color: #ccc;">  I pointed out</a>=C2=A0that there was not a sing=
le dollar sign in the investor presentation. I said:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I think that a more realistic valu=
ation method here is not to worry about cash flows at all =E2=80=94=C2=A0<e=
m>as Trump SPAC clearly does not=C2=A0</em>=E2=80=94 and treat the stock si=
mply as a token of public interest in Donald Trump. My guess is that the pr=
ice of Trump SPAC stock will not, for instance, be much affected by its ear=
nings announcements, unless Trump himself does the earnings calls in which =
case it will go up no matter what he says. =E2=80=A6=C2=A0My guess is that =
each day that goes by without Trump news, the stock will go down a bit. My =
guess is that the stock is essentially a bet on Trump=E2=80=99s personal ne=
wsiness, on Trump-news volatility.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I suppose that was wrong, specifically, in tha=
t the stock was down 22% today on spectacularly bad earnings, but I do thin=
k it was right in spirit. After those earnings, Trump Media is trading at o=
nly like 1,500 times revenues. It=E2=80=99s just not about the earnings!</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One other important point=C2=A0from Lipschultz=
=E2=80=99s article:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The heightened valuation has made =
it costly and risky to bet against with short sellers facing annual financi=
ng costs of 500% to borrow, according to brokerages. That makes it the most=
 expensive US company to bet against with over $100 million of short intere=
st by a large margin, data from financial analytics firm S3 Partners show.<=
/p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Again, fundamental value is a=C2=A0<em>floor=
=C2=A0</em>on stock price, but not a ceiling. If you think that a stock is =
overvalued, you can=E2=80=99t do anything to force it down to fair value. Y=
ou can=E2=80=99t just short unlimited shares: You have to borrow them, and =
pay 500% per year to do so, and not many shares are available to borrow. Bu=
t even if you could short all you wanted for free, people could keep buying=
 them! The price could keep going up. It=E2=80=99s possible that the old ru=
les of fundamental value still apply. But are you sure?</p>
