5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBbacd8756" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscop=
e=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">golf buddy</a> or forme=
r baseball teammate of a corporate employee=C2=A0(or banker, lawyer, etc.) =
has a duty of trust and confidence to the employee, and is not supposed to =
use inside information to trade her company=E2=80=99s=C2=A0stock. (And a ro=
mantic partner=C2=A0of an employee=C2=A0of an=C2=A0acquirer=C2=A0is not sup=
posed to use inside information to trade the target=E2=80=99s stock.)</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You need=C2=A0<em>something</em>, some duty to=
 keep the information confidential. Famously, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/34887393.257355/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmN=
vbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTgtMTItMDMvaW5zaWRlci10cmFkaW5nLWluLXRoZS1wb3=
RhdG8tdHJhZGU_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDQwMTI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1d=
G1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwNDAxJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0=
dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB09b739f9" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D=
"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  in the US</a>, if you ove=
rhear a banker talking about a deal on a train, you can go ahead and trade =
on that. (Not legal advice!) What makes the insider trading illegal is the =
breach of a duty, not=C2=A0<em>just=C2=A0</em>the inside information.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The US Securities and Exchange Commission does=
 keep trying to expand the boundaries, though. We have <a href=3D"https://l=
ink.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34887393.257355/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb2=
